old text-brand-800 pr-4\"> How to enable Whitelist Mode? </h2> <svg class=\"w-5 h-5 text-brand-400 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"> <path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" d=\"M19 9l-7 7-7-7\"></path> </svg> </summary> <div class=\"px-6 pb-6 md:px-8 md:pb-8 -mt-2\"> <div class=\"text-warm-600 leading-relaxed\"> <strong>Whitelist Mode</strong> can be enabled in the <strong>Focus Mode</strong> within Settings. When selecting apps, avoid selecting entire categories. If an entire category is selected, the whitelist mode will become invalid. If a category contains only one app, or if all apps in a category are selected, the category will be automatically selected. In this case, downloading another app in that category can solve the problem. </div> </div> </details> <!-- Question 2 --> <details class=\"group bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl border border-warm-200/50 shadow-sm shadow-warm-200/20 overflow-hidden\"> <summary class=\"flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 md:p-8 select-none\"> <h2 class=\"text-lg font-semibold text-brand-800 pr-4\"> Why can some apps still be used even if they are not on the whitelist? </h2> <svg class=\"w-5 h-5 text-brand-400 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"> <path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" d=\"M19 9l-7 7-7-7\"></path> </svg> </summary> <div class=\"px-6 pb-6 md:px-8 md:pb-8 -mt-2\"> <div class=\"text-warm-600 leading-relaxed\"> If you have set <strong>Screen Time</strong> limits for an app and then choose to <strong>\"Ignore Limit\"</strong> for that day, the app will no longer be restricted by <strong>Cat on Chair</strong>. </div> </div> </details> <!-- Question 3 (Family Sharing) --> <details class=\"group bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl border border-warm-200/50 shadow-sm shadow-warm-200/20 overflow-hidden\"> <summary class=\"flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 md:p-8 select-none\"> <h2 class=\"text-lg font-semibold text-brand-800 pr-4\"> How do I share with family members after purchasing a Family Sharing membership? </h2> <svg class=\"w-5 h-5 text-brand-400 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"> <path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" d=\"M19 9l-7 7-7-7\"></path> </svg> </summary> <div class=\"px-6 pb-6 md:px-8 md:pb-8 -mt-2\"> <div class=\"text-warm-600 leading-relaxed\"> Since our Family Sharing is built on Apple's <strong>iCloud Family</strong> system, all members must be in the same iCloud Family. Annual family subscriptions share automatically with family members. For <strong>Lifetime Family</strong> membership, you need to enable <strong>\"Share My Purchases\"</strong>. We recommend sharing with family members or close friends you know privately. Please be careful with your personal and financial security if sharing with strangers. </div> </div> </details> <!-- Question 4 (Android) --> <details class=\"group bg-white/80 backdrop-blur-sm rounded-2xl border border-warm-200/50 shadow-sm shadow-warm-200/20 overflow-hidden\"> <summary class=\"flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 md:p-8 select-none\"> <h2 class=\"text-lg font-semibold text-brand-800 pr-4\"> Is there an Android version? </h2> <svg class=\"w-5 h-5 text-brand-400 flex-shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"> <path stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" stroke-width=\"2\" d=\"M19 9l-7 7-7-7\"></path> </svg> </summary> <div class=\"px-6 pb-6 md:px-8 md:pb-8 -mt-2\"> <div class=\"text-warm-600 leading-relaxed\"> Currently, our resources are limited, and we cannot support Android development. We plan to focus on perfecting the